<subSubSection id="AF965CD435030D335ED0882C45A1F9CE" pageId="1" pageNumber="292" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="E7330F5F35030D335ED0882C41DCFB3B" blockId="1.[136,1452,1108,1603]" pageId="1" pageNumber="292">
<emphasis id="D5F8D34D35030D335ED0882C40A6FB1E" bold="true" box="[189,414,1144,1170]" pageId="1" pageNumber="292">Material examined</emphasis>
:— 
<collectingCountry id="9F9B4FCF35030D335FD2882C4312FB1E" box="[447,554,1144,1170]" name="Brazil" pageId="1" pageNumber="292">BRAZIL</collectingCountry>
. Pantanal dos Marimbus,Andaraí, 
<collectingRegion id="2548C1BD35030D335DC4882C4513FB1E" box="[937,1067,1144,1170]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="1" pageNumber="292">Bahia State</collectingRegion>
. Sample: 
<collectionCode id="819D979A35030D335AF8882C45D6FB1E" box="[1173,1262,1144,1170]" country="Brazil" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15506" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15506" name="Universidade Estadual de Feira de Santana" pageId="1" pageNumber="292" type="Herbarium">HUEFS</collectionCode>
185370, 
<collectionCode id="819D979A35030D335B3E882C4494FB1E" box="[1363,1452,1144,1170]" country="Brazil" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15506" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15506" name="Universidade Estadual de Feira de Santana" pageId="1" pageNumber="292" type="Herbarium">HUEFS</collectionCode>
185390.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E7330F5F35030D335ED088944258FB57" blockId="1.[136,1452,1108,1603]" box="[189,864,1216,1243]" pageId="1" pageNumber="292">
<emphasis id="D5F8D34D35030D335ED088944021FB56" bold="true" box="[189,281,1216,1242]" pageId="1" pageNumber="292">Habitat</emphasis>
:—It was found on 
<taxonomicName id="208C74DC35030D335F9E889443FDFB56" box="[499,709,1216,1242]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lentibulariaceae" genus="Utricularia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="1" pageNumber="292" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="foliosa">
<emphasis id="D5F8D34D35030D335F9E889443FDFB56" box="[499,709,1216,1242]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="292">Utricularia foliosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(periphyton).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E7330F5F35030D335ED088B0428FFA02" blockId="1.[136,1452,1108,1603]" pageId="1" pageNumber="292">
<emphasis id="D5F8D34D35030D335ED088B041CDFB72" bold="true" box="[189,245,1252,1278]" pageId="1" pageNumber="292">Note</emphasis>
:— 
<materialsCitation id="57E4050235030D335F7A88B0428BFA02" country="French Guiana" location="South America" pageId="1" pageNumber="292" specimenCount="1">
This variety, probably endemic to 
<location id="E253598435030D335CCF88B04275FB72" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:6F25BE4935030D335EE5885845A1F9CE:E253598435030D335CCF88B04275FB72" box="[674,845,1252,1278]" country="French Guiana" name="South America" pageId="1" pageNumber="292">South America</location>
, is characterized in having rounded semicells, closed sinus, cell wall locally remarkably thickened and ornamented by scrobicles. Regarding this latter morphological feature, Thérezién reported scrobicles only at the central protuberance and the margins. In the Brazilian specimens, the whole cell wall is ornamented by those scrobiculations, and the cells are slightly longer. The 
<taxonomicName id="208C74DC35030D335AF48905446BFAE6" box="[1177,1363,1361,1387]" pageId="1" pageNumber="292" rank="variety" variety="incrasstaum">
var. 
<emphasis id="D5F8D34D35030D335AA78905446BFAE6" box="[1226,1363,1361,1386]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="292">incrasstaum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is quite rare and till now it was only known to its 
<typeStatus id="3837B1FD35030D335C36892143B3FA03" box="[603,651,1397,1423]" pageId="1" pageNumber="292">type</typeStatus>
locality in 
<collectingCountry id="9F9B4FCF35030D335D678920428BFA02" box="[778,947,1396,1422]" name="French Guiana" pageId="1" pageNumber="292">French Guiana</collectingCountry>
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E7330F5F35030D335ED089CC45A1F9CE" blockId="1.[136,1452,1108,1603]" pageId="1" pageNumber="292">
Another 
<taxonomicName id="208C74DC35030D335F4889CC4090FA3E" authorityName="Corda ex Ralfs" authorityYear="1848" box="[293,424,1432,1458]" class="Conjugatophyceae" family="Desmidiaceae" genus="Cosmarium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Zygnematales" pageId="1" pageNumber="292" phylum="Charophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D5F8D34D35030D335F4889CC4090FA3E" box="[293,424,1432,1458]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="292">Cosmarium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
taxon which was apparently endemic to that country was recently reported also in the Marimbus, 
<collectingCountry id="9F9B4FCF35030D335F6689E8406CFA5A" box="[267,340,1468,1494]" name="Brazil" pageId="1" pageNumber="292">Brazil</collectingCountry>
: 
<taxonomicName id="208C74DC35030D335F0C89E84569FA5B" authority="Therezien (1985: 85)" authorityName="Therezien" authorityPageNumber="85" authorityYear="1985" box="[353,1105,1468,1495]" class="Conjugatophyceae" family="Desmidiaceae" genus="Cosmarium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Zygnematales" pageId="1" pageNumber="292" phylum="Charophyta" rank="variety" species="anisochondrum" variety="isthmolatum">
<emphasis id="D5F8D34D35030D335F0C89E843A3FA5A" box="[353,667,1468,1494]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="292">Cosmarium anisochondrum</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis id="D5F8D34D35030D335CBA89E84259FA5A" box="[727,865,1468,1494]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="292">isthmolatum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="831D72AE35030D335D0789E84569FA5B" author="Therezien, Y." box="[874,1105,1468,1495]" pageId="1" pageNumber="292" pagination="5 - 275" refId="ref5633" refString="Therezien, Y. (1985) Contribution a l'etude des algues d'eau douce de la Guyane Francaise (a l'exclusion des Diatomees). Bibliotheca Phycologica 72: 5 - 275." type="journal article" year="1985">Thérézien (1985:85)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="831D72AE35030D335A0F89E84403FA5A" author="Ramos, G. J. P. &amp; Santos, M. &amp; Moura, C. W. N." box="[1122,1339,1468,1494]" pageId="1" pageNumber="292" refId="ref5485" refString="Ramos, G. J. P., Santos, M. A &amp; Moura, C. W. N. (2021) How hidden is the diversity of the genus Cosmarium (Desmidiaceae) in the Brazilian Caatinga? Acta Botanica Brasilica. [in press]" type="book" year="2021">
Ramos 
<emphasis id="D5F8D34D35030D335AD689E945CEFA5A" box="[1211,1270,1468,1494]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="292">et al.</emphasis>
2021
</bibRefCitation>
). Overall, there are other rare desmids co-occurring in 
<collectingCountry id="9F9B4FCF35030D335C1689B4421AFA76" box="[635,802,1504,1530]" name="French Guiana" pageId="1" pageNumber="292">French Guiana</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="9F9B4FCF35030D335D3489B44298FA76" box="[857,928,1504,1530]" name="Brazil" pageId="1" pageNumber="292">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, especially in the Chapada Diamantina region, such as 
<taxonomicName id="208C74DC35030D335EB28A5142ACF992" authority="Therezien (1985: 82)" authorityName="Therezien" authorityPageNumber="82" authorityYear="1985" box="[223,916,1540,1567]" class="Conjugatophyceae" family="Desmidiaceae" genus="Euastrum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Zygnematales" pageId="1" pageNumber="292" phylum="Charophyta" rank="variety" species="subcyclopicum" variety="elongatum">
<emphasis id="D5F8D34D35030D335EB28A5140C0F992" box="[223,504,1540,1566]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="292">Euastrum subcyclopicum</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis id="D5F8D34D35030D335C438A50439CF992" box="[558,676,1540,1566]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="292">elongatum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="831D72AE35030D335CC78A5042ACF992" author="Therezien, Y." box="[682,916,1540,1567]" pageId="1" pageNumber="292" pagination="5 - 275" refId="ref5633" refString="Therezien, Y. (1985) Contribution a l'etude des algues d'eau douce de la Guyane Francaise (a l'exclusion des Diatomees). Bibliotheca Phycologica 72: 5 - 275." type="journal article" year="1985">Thérézien (1985: 82)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="831D72AE35030D335DCF8A50454AF992" author="Ramos, G. J. P. &amp; Costa, F. M. &amp; Santos, M. A. &amp; Moura, C. W. N." box="[930,1138,1540,1566]" pageId="1" pageNumber="292" pagination="185 - 196" refId="ref5352" refString="Ramos, G. J. P., Costa, F. M., Santos, M. A. &amp; Moura, C. W. N. (2019) Taxonomic novelties, new records, and rare species of desmids from the Chapada Diamantina region, Brazil. Phytotaxa 391 (3): 185 - 196. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / phytotaxa. 391.3.2" type="journal article" year="2019">
Ramos 
<emphasis id="D5F8D34D35030D335D9A8A514517F992" box="[1015,1071,1540,1566]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="292">et al.</emphasis>
2019
</bibRefCitation>
). However, more studies are recommended to investigate such similarity between the desmid flora of those two countries.
</paragraph>
